1. The
Types of Personal Information We Use
This
section describes the different types of personal information we collect from
you and how we collect it.
If
you would like to know more about specific types of data and how we use that
data, please see the section entitled “
How we use your personal
information
”
below.
The
following is a high level summary of the types of personal information we use:
Game
1.
Information you provide to us (either directly or through a third party).
Account
     registration information:
You give us your nickname when you log-in as a
     ‘guest’ in order to use the Service. If you login via your Google Play
     account, you give us your Google ID and Google display name. If you login
     via your Apple (iOS game centre) account, you give us your Apple ID, Apple
     display name and profile picture. If you login via your Facebook account,
     you give us your Facebook username and ID and you may choose to give us
     your email address and friends list as well. You may also choose to
     provide your gender during account registration.
Validation
     data
:
     When you register for an account for the Service we will process certain
     information to validate your eligibility for the Service.
Survey
     information (aggregated data):
If you choose to participate in a
     survey about the Service, you may be asked to provide certain personal
     information, e.g. your age, gender, email, address, phone number
     geographic (country) location, game information (game habits and
     preferences) and any other content you choose to provide as part of the
     survey response. We will use your survey response the purpose of improving
     the Service. In such case, your personal data will be processed in
     accordance with iMUR’s
privacy policy
. We will only process
     your aggregated information which we receive from the iMUR platform once
     you complete the survey and for the purpose of improving the Service.
Marketing
     information
:
     Advertising information about you that we collect directly from you and
     from third party ad partners (e.g. Facebook and Google) via a third party
     SDK (Appsflyer), such as your IP address, IDFA, Android advertising ID
     (AAID), which users click/view
our
campaign and creative materials,
     e.g. photos and videos that are advertised on the ad partner’s platform,
     your advertising ID and other user engagement data (purchase behaviour and
     in-app behaviour) (collectively, “
advertising identifiers
”),
     Facebook campaign ID, user search terms and Google Adwords campaign
     information and identifiers. We also collect certain advertising
     information about you which we share with third party ad partners (e.g.
     Facebook and Google) via a third party SDK (Appsflyer and Adjust) to
     monitor the success of our advertising campaigns, such as your advertising
     identifiers, user in-game activities (including login, purchase
     activities, friends invited and user retention) and other tracking
     information (mobile device IDs, hashed email addresses, demographic or
     interest data, and content viewed or actions taken on a website / app).
Forum
     (website only) information:
If you choose to use and post on a forum, your
     username, password, email address and the content of your forum posts and
     messages.
2.
Information
about you
generated as part of the
Service
We
automatically collect certain data from you when you use the Service, namely:
·
IP address and open ID
to facilitate account
registration;
·
game data and log
information
:
open ID, IP address, device model, geographic ranking based on your selected country
location and information regarding your use of the Service, such as gameplay
statistics (e.g. level, heroes and scores);
·
GPS information
to enable you to find users
near you
;
·
game analytics information
: your user region and
device information to enable us to perform overall game analytics, including
error fixing, troubleshooting and debugging;
·
transaction records
: when you make purchases
within the Service, your Open ID, product cost, product purchased, IP address,
device information (OS version, phone model, device root status) and details of
transactions linked to your player ID;
your
text and audio chat data
when you communicate with other users in
     the Service (including if you use text-translation services or
     voice-to-chat functions when you communicate with other users in the
     Service);
gameplay
     video
if you choose to download or share your gameplay;
for
     the purposes of providing customer suppor
t (in-app or via email): name,
     open ID, device ID, application version, battery level, WiFi strength,
     free space on phone, network type, iOS version, platform and network type,
     carrier, country code and any photos that you may wish to upload to
     illustrate your problem;
for
     the purposes of sending you push notifications
while using the Service: your
     device model, device name, device manufacturer, running process
     information, SDK version, application package name, application version, operator
     name and network type;
security
     information
:
     your device (iOS or Android)’s technical device information, for the
     purposes of detecting and preventing cheating and
any domain name hijacking on the
     Service
;
anti-cheating
     security information:
your
     game speed, whether in-game tools are functioning within the normal
     parameter, account, access time, for the purpose of detecting and
     preventing cheating on the Service; and
In-game
     forum information:
Your
     user ID, nickname, profile picture, comments left by you on the forum, in
     order to facilitate the posting of your comments on the forum.
eSports
Website
account login information
: In order to access
     the eSports Website, you must login via your Apple, Facebook or Google
     account used to register for the Game. If you login via your Google Play
     account, Apple (iOS game centre) account or VK account, you give us your
     user ID, nickname, profile picture, user token and Open ID. If you login
     via your Facebook account, you give us your Facebook UID, name, profile picture,
     user token and Open ID;
competition information
: Your Open ID,
     nickname, profile picture;
game
     data and log information:
as above in the “Game” section, which is also
     processed to provide you with feedback and information about your gameplay
     and progress during our eSport competitions;
your
text chat data
when you communicate with your team mates;
data
     reporting information:
your user ID, client type, nation, battle ID, match
     ID, area ID, target user ID, channel ID and push ID;
your
Game ID
and
email address
; and
prize
     distribution information:
Consignee name, phone number, address and bank card
     details (for monetary prizes).
Cookies
We
use cookies and other similar technologies (e.g. web beacons, log files,
scripts and eTags) (“
Cookies
”) to enhance your experience using the Service.
Cookies are small files which, when placed on your device, enable us to provide
certain features and functionality.
For
more information about our Cookies policy, click
here
.
Children
Our
Service is not intended for children, unless their parent or legal guardian has
provided consent (if this is available in your jurisdiction). Except with such
consent, children must not use the Service for any purpose. If you are a parent
of a child who has signed up with your consent and you would like to understand
more about the Service or how you can revoke your consent, please refer to the
section “
Information for Parents
” below.
By
children, we mean users under the age of 13 years old; or in the case of a
country where the minimum age for processing personal information differs, such
different age. For users located in certain countries, we have listed the
relevant minimum age in the table below.
