Necessary
  to perform our contract with you to provide the Service.
Security
  information:
·
Android:
device root status, list
  of installed hack software, list of running hack software, hash values of
  game files (encrypted), host file tampered, running in Android simulator,
  Android SDK API Level, equipment boot time, equipment brand and model, CPU
  structure and CPU model, resolution, Sensor status, device kernel version,
  country code, language, available memory and available space, internet type
  (WiFi/4G/3G)
·
iOS:
device jailbreaking
  status, hash values of game files (encrypted), host file tampered, IDFV,
  equipment brand and model, iOS version, Internet type (WiFi/4G/3G)
We use this information
  to detect and prevent cheating and any domain name hijacking on the Service.
It
  is in our legitimate interest to ensure the security of our services and to
  maintain a fair gaming environment within the Service.
Anti-Cheating
  Security information:
your
  game data (such as game speed and use of in-game tools), account, access time
We use this information
  to detect and prevent cheating on the Service.
It
  is in our legitimate interest to ensure the security of our services and to
  maintain a fair gaming environment within the Service.
In-game
  forum information (via Arena Buddy):
This consists of information you
  make publicly available to other users of the Service when you post any
  comments on the forum on the Service, comprising: Your user ID, nickname,
  profile picture, comments left by you on the forum
Please
  note the in-game forum on the Service is interoperable with Arena Buddy – any
  content you post on the in-game forum can be viewed on Arena Buddy, and vice
  versa.
To
