Welcome to the IEG Market and User Research Survey!
This privacy policy explains the when, how and why when it comes to the processing of your personal information in connection with a survey made available by us each, a “
Survey
”, and sets out your choices and rights in relation to that information. Please read it carefully – it is important for you to understand how we collect and use your information, and how you can control it.
If you do not agree to the processing of your personal information in the way this privacy policy describes, please do not provide your information when requested and do not participate in a Survey. Where applicable, by participating in the Survey you are accepting our rules regarding your personal information as described in this privacy policy.
This Survey is operated by Proxima Beta Pte. Limited “
IEG
” “
we
”, “
us
”, “
our
”. For the purpose of EU data protection laws, we are the data controller.
Proxima Beta Pte. Limited is a company registered in Singapore with its office located at 10 Anson Road #21-07 International Plaza, Singapore 079903. Our data protection officer can be contacted at
DPO_imursurvey@weisurvey.com
.
The Types of Personal Information We Use
This section describes the different types of personal information we collect from you and how we collect it. If you would like to know more about specific types of data and how we use that data, please see the section entitled “
How We Use Your Personal Information
” below.
The following is a high level summary of the types of personal information we use:
Information you provide to us directly as part of the Survey
You give us information about you when you take the Survey, comprising the responses to each question in the Survey, which may reveal your WeChat or QQ open ID, gender, age or age range, date of birth, country or region of residency, income information, education data and phone number, email address.
Information we collect when you participate in a Survey
We will process your IP address, browser version and operating system version in order to optimise and provide the Survey. Your IP address, in particular, is only used for identifying your suggested location.
Cookies
We use cookies and other similar technologies e.g. web beacons, log files, scripts and eTags “
Cookies
” to enhance your experience using the Survey, to which you may be directed if you use the Survey’s customer support features. Cookies are small files which, when placed on your device, enable us to provide certain features and functionality.
You have the option to permit installation of such Cookies or subsequently disable them. You may accept all cookies, or instruct the device to provide notice at the time of installation of cookies, or refuse to accept all cookies by adjusting the relevant cookie retention function in your device. However, in the event of your refusal to install cookies, the Survey or part of the Survey may be unable to operate as designed.
For more information about our Cookies policy, click
here
.
Children
The Survey is not intended for children. Children must not participate in the Survey. By children, we mean users under the age of 16 years old; or in the case of users located in in the countries specified below, the specified age.
If you are over the age of 16 years old but under the age stipulated below for the country where you are located, you need the consent of your parent or guardian before participating in the Survey.
